review_blob:
Nose: roast coffee, dark roasted malt. Occasional floral/herbal notes. 

Taste: lots of dark roast coffee. Just enough bittering hops. Good mouth feel, not too syrupy.

Appearance: nice medium dark copper, cream color head. 

Nose: vanilla from the oak. Some hops peek through. 

Taste: Can definitely pick out oak influence - vanilla, dark caramel. Toasted nuts. Bittering hops balance things out. Not too sweet or overdone. Nice medium mouth feel.
beer_name: Widmer Brothers Reserve Barrel Aged Brrrbon

review_blob:
Appearance: Dark brown with reddish tint. 

Nose: Toasted nuts, toasted bread.

Taste: Smooth mouth feel. Chocolate and dark, almost scorched caramel. Toasted nuts. Just enough hops to balance.

Nose: cocoa, muted dank hops (not in a bad way, just not bright and citrusy). Taste: initial hit is cocoa, unexpectedly. Good level of hop bitterness. Balances malt nicely. Again, less citrusy to my palate.
